4. Relationships
One-to-Many (1:N)
One Instructor (User) → many Courses
One Course → many StudentProfiles
One Course → many MatchRuns
One MatchRun → many Teams
One Team → many TeamMembers
One StudentProfile → many CheckIns / Contributions
Many-to-Many (M:N)
Students ↔ Skills
A student can have multiple skills
A skill can belong to multiple students
Resolved by: StudentSkills
Teams ↔ Students
A team has many students
A student belongs to one team per run
Resolved by: TeamMembers
One-to-One (1:1)
Each MatchRun has associated RunLogs (logical grouping per run)
