6. Short Explanation

The TeamMatch database is designed to support structured team formation while maintaining data integrity and scalability. Core entities such as Users, Courses, and StudentProfiles capture essential system data, while junction tables like StudentSkills and TeamMembers resolve many-to-many relationships efficiently. This ensures that skills, team assignments, and participation data are stored without redundancy.

Foreign keys enforce relationships between entities, allowing the system to maintain consistency across modules such as team generation, contribution tracking, and analytics. The design supports deterministic team formation, instructor configuration, and real-time updates, making it both efficient and scalable for classroom environments.

7. Design Justification
No data duplication → normalized structure (skills, teams, profiles separated)
Scalable → supports large classes and multiple match runs
Flexible → allows instructor overrides and changing constraints
Efficient querying → optimized relationships for dashboards and analytics
Aligned with FRD → supports all required features (team formation, tracking, explainability)
